## SEO (SSR, sitemap, canonical)

Implemented in [src/server.ts](src/server.ts). Audits: `.cursor/skills/seo/SKILL.md`, `.cursor/rules/seo.mdc`.

### Crawl files

| Path | Notes |
|------|--------|
| `/robots.txt`, `/api/robots` | Allow `/`; disallow `/profile`, `/projects`, `/admin`; `Sitemap:` absolute URL |
| `/sitemap.xml`, `/api/sitemap` | Also [api/sitemap.ts](api/sitemap.ts) on Vercel |

### Sitemap contents and limits

- `/` (priority 1.0) plus static: `/about`, `/contact`, `/privacy`, `/terms`, `/catalog`
- Each published publication: `/p/{slugOrId}` (up to **1000** from `listPublicationsPublic`)
- First **translated** chapter reading URL for at most **100** publications (`SITEMAP_CHAPTER_PUBS_LIMIT`)

### SSR HTML (meta for crawlers)

| Path | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| `/`, `/catalog`, `/about`, `/contact`, `/privacy`, `/terms` | `serveStaticPageHtml` — title, description, og, canonical |
| `/catalog` | Canonical URL = site root `/` (avoid duplicate home vs catalog) |
| `/p/:publicationId` | `servePublicationHtml` — meta, hidden `<main class="publication-page-seo">`, Book + BreadcrumbList JSON-LD |
| `/p/:publicationId/chapters/:chapterId/reading` | Chapter title/description; chapter breadcrumb |

Client navigation updates head via [usePageMeta.ts](src/client/hooks/usePageMeta.ts); direct loads and bots rely on SSR above.

### Vercel rewrites

In [vercel.json](vercel.json), `/`, `/catalog`, `/about`, `/contact`, `/privacy`, `/terms`, and `/p/*` route to `api/index` (Express SSR). Other SPA paths fall through to static `index.html`.

### Auth areas

`/projects/*`, `/profile`, `/admin/*` are disallowed in robots and not in sitemap (author workspace, not public SEO targets).

